      "id": "review::.::holistic::cross_module_architecture::provider_config_contract_drift",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 1,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "The documented runtime provider-config boundary has drifted into a backend/frontend-specific loose shape.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
        "related_files": [
          "docs/specs/2026-03-13-microsoft-sso-design.md",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/controller/ProviderConfigController.java",
          "frontend/src/types/auth.ts",
          "frontend/src/hooks/useProviderConfig.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "The design document requires `/api/auth/providers` to return a stable schema where disabled Microsoft config is still represented explicitly with `null`/empty values.",
          "`ProviderConfigController.getProviders()` only adds Microsoft `clientId` and `authority` when Microsoft client-side login is enabled, so disabled and enabled responses have different shapes.",
          "`normalizeProviderConfig()` accepts partial objects and backfills defaults on the frontend, which means the consumer is compensating for a drifting boundary instead of enforcing one published contract."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Replace the stringly `Map<String, Object>` provider payload with a typed backend DTO that always emits the full schema, and have the frontend consume that exact contract without partial-object normalization.",
