    "review::.::holistic::api_surface_coherence::provider_verification_mixed_abstraction_levels": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::api_surface_coherence::provider_verification_mixed_abstraction_levels",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 2,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "Provider verification APIs expose three different contract layers for the same job",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "api_surface_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/GoogleTokenVerifier.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/MicrosoftTokenVerifier.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/ProviderIdentityNormalizer.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/OAuth2SuccessHandler.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/controller/AuthController.java"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`GoogleTokenVerifier.verify(String)` returns the vendor-specific `GoogleIdToken.Payload`, and callers then unpack fields to call `ProviderIdentityNormalizer.normalizeGoogleClaims(String googleId, String email, String name, String pictureUrl, AuthFlow loginFlow)`.",
          "`MicrosoftTokenVerifier.verifyIdToken(String credential, String expectedNonce, AuthFlow authFlow)` already returns `NormalizedIdentity`, while `ProviderIdentityNormalizer.normalizeMicrosoftClaims(Map<String, Object> claims, AuthFlow loginFlow)` accepts a raw claims map on other code paths.",
          "Similar 'verify an identity and hand it to user creation' flows therefore make callers remember three different public contract shapes: provider payload, raw claim map, and already-normalized domain object."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Choose one public contract level for provider adapters\u2014either have both verifiers return `NormalizedIdentity`, or have both expose typed raw claims and let one normalizer own the mapping\u2014so Google and Microsoft flows can be used with the same mental model.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "2f0f4296"
      },
      "status": "fixed",
      "note": "GoogleTokenVerifier now returns VerifiedGoogleIdentity (a provider-neutral record) instead of GoogleIdToken.Payload. AuthController no longer imports or depends on the Google API library \u2014 all Google SDK types are encapsulated in GoogleTokenVerifier.",
      "first_seen": "2026-03-14T19:10:42+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-14T19:10:42+00:00",
      "resolved_at": "2026-03-14T20:51:41+00:00",
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "work_item_kind": "review_defect",
      "issue_kind": "review_defect",
      "origin": "review_import",
      "lang": "java",
      "suppressed": false,
      "suppressed_at": null,
      "suppression_pattern": null,
      "resolution_attestation": {
        "kind": "manual",
        "text": "I have actually GoogleTokenVerifier now returns VerifiedGoogleIdentity (a provider-neutral record) instead of GoogleIdToken.Payload. AuthController no longer imports or depends on the Google API library \u2014 all Google SDK types are encapsulated in GoogleTokenVerifier. and I am not gaming the score.",
        "attested_at": "2026-03-14T20:51:41+00:00",
        "scan_verified": false
      }
    },
    "review::.::holistic::api_surface_coherence::jwt_token_generation_contract_is_hidden_by_overloads": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::api_surface_coherence::jwt_token_generation_contract_is_hidden_by_overloads",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 1,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "`JwtTokenService.generateToken` overloads hide which token schema a caller receives",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "api_surface_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/JwtTokenService.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/controller/AuthController.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/OAuth2SuccessHandler.java",
          "backend/src/test/java/com/demo/sso/controller/ControllerIntegrationTest.java"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`JwtTokenService.generateToken(String email, String googleId)` always builds the legacy subject/`googleId` token, while `generateToken(User user)` conditionally emits V2 claims or delegates back to the legacy overload depending on rollout settings.",
          "The shared method name `generateToken` does not tell callers whether the result will contain legacy `googleId` claims or V2 `ver`/`provider`/`providerUserId`/`email` claims, and production callers use a different overload than several integration tests."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Split legacy and current minting into explicitly named entrypoints (for example `generateLegacyToken(...)` and `generateUserToken(...)`) and keep only one default public path for production callers so the token contract is obvious from the call site.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "f0fd48cb"
      },
      "status": "fixed",
      "note": "Renamed generateToken(String,String) to generateLegacyToken, made package-private. Public API now only exposes generateToken(User) which delegates based on rollout mode.",
      "first_seen": "2026-03-14T19:10:42+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-14T19:10:42+00:00",
      "resolved_at": "2026-03-14T20:45:20+00:00",
