      "id": "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::use_provider_config_silent_swallow",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 1,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "useProviderConfig silently discards all fetch errors without logging or user feedback",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "error_consistency",
        "related_files": [
          "frontend/src/hooks/useProviderConfig.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "Line 22: .catch(() => { ... setProviderConfig(DEFAULT_PROVIDER_CONFIG); }) \u2014 the error argument is not even captured",
          "Unlike useAuth.ts which distinguishes error types and logs warnings, useProviderConfig discards the error object entirely",
          "If the /auth/providers endpoint is down or returns malformed JSON, the user sees a silently degraded UI with no indication that the configuration is stale or incomplete"
        ],
        "suggestion": "At minimum, add console.warn('Failed to fetch provider config:', err) to preserve diagnostic information. Consider adding an error state so consuming components can indicate when config is from defaults rather than the backend.",
