    "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::rollout_mode_leaks_into_store_layer": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::rollout_mode_leaks_into_store_layer",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 2,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "RedisAuthCodeStore queries AuthRolloutProperties per-call to resolve key prefix and lookup order, leaking rollout semantics through the store abstraction boundary",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
        "related_files": [
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/challenge/RedisAuthCodeStore.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/config/AuthRolloutProperties.java"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "RedisAuthCodeStore.exchangeCode() switches on rolloutProperties.getIdentityContractMode() to decide V2_ONLY vs LEGACY_ONLY vs COMPATIBILITY lookup order \u2014 the store must understand rollout semantics to select its Redis key prefix",
          "currentWritePrefix() branches on rolloutProperties.getJwtMintMode() \u2014 the write path similarly depends on rollout state",
          "The AuthCodeStore interface contract (storeJwt/exchangeCode) makes no mention of rollout modes, so the abstraction boundary is honest at the interface level but leaky at the implementation level"
        ],
        "suggestion": "Inject a resolved key-prefix strategy (e.g., a small record or enum) at construction time rather than having the store query rollout properties per-call. This would make the migration mode a construction-time decision rather than a runtime branch on every store/exchange operation.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "77bc40ae"
      },
      "status": "wontfix",
      "note": "All three are significant architectural changes requiring new test infrastructure or fundamental provider wiring redesign \u2014 beyond code quality improvement scope",
