      "id": "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::authenticated_identity_nullable_modeling",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 2,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "AuthenticatedUserIdentity models two mutually exclusive contract versions via nullable fields instead of a sealed type hierarchy",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
        "related_files": [
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/model/AuthenticatedUserIdentity.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/token/JwtTokenService.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/user/UserService.java"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "AuthenticatedUserIdentity has 6 fields where userId/provider/providerUserId are null for legacy and legacyProviderKey is null for v2 \u2014 the nullability is structural, not exceptional",
          "Callers must use isLegacy() to determine which fields are safe to access \u2014 JwtTokenService.parseAuthenticatedUser builds either variant, UserService.findCurrentUser branches on isLegacy()",
          "The code itself contains a comment: 'Future: consider refactoring to a sealed interface with LegacyIdentity and V2Identity record implementations'",
          "Previous review issue on this topic was marked 'fixed' but the structural pattern persists \u2014 the fix appears to have been documentation improvement (javadoc and comment), not the type-level refactoring"
        ],
        "suggestion": "Refactor to a sealed interface AuthenticatedUserIdentity with LegacyIdentity and V2Identity record implementations. This would make the contract version a compile-time guarantee, eliminate nullable fields, and let callers use pattern matching instead of isLegacy() checks.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "cb94ebb8"
      },
      "status": "wontfix",
