      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 1,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "AuthenticatedUserIdentity dual-nullable design forces runtime isLegacy() branching in UserService and UserController instead of type-level dispatch",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "mid_level_elegance",
        "related_files": [
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/model/AuthenticatedUserIdentity.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/user/UserService.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/controller/UserController.java"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "UserService.findCurrentUser branches: if (identity.isLegacy()) \u2192 findByEmail, else \u2192 findById. UserController.getCurrentUser branches: if (principal instanceof AuthenticatedUserIdentity) vs legacy fallback construction.",
          "The record has a comment 'Future: consider refactoring to a sealed interface with LegacyIdentity and V2Identity' acknowledging this as known debt.",
          "Every consumer at the handoff boundary must perform variant detection manually, creating a predictability cost at integration seams."
