          "AuthApiResponse is a sealed interface with four implementations: TokenResponse has 'token', ErrorResponse has 'error', LogoutResponse has 'message', MicrosoftChallengeResponse has 'challengeId'+'nonce'. A frontend consumer cannot distinguish response type by the presence of a single key without trying multiple field names or using HTTP status codes."
