    "review::.::holistic::contract_coherence::findorcreate_hidden_mutation": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::contract_coherence::findorcreate_hidden_mutation",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 1,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "UserService.findOrCreateUser silently mutates existing user records despite 'findOrCreate' naming",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "contract_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/user/UserService.java"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "Method name is 'findOrCreateUser' suggesting two behaviors: find or create",
          "Lines 36-38: when user is found, delegates to 'updateExistingUser' which overwrites email, name, pictureUrl, provider identity fields, and lastLoginAt",
          "The update-on-find behavior is a hidden side effect \u2014 callers (AuthCompletionService line 40) expect find-or-create semantics, not find-update-or-create"
        ],
        "suggestion": "Rename to 'findOrCreateAndUpdate' or 'syncUser' to make the mutation behavior explicit. Alternatively, add Javadoc documenting that existing users are always updated with latest identity claims on login.",
